<tr>
<td class="newsbody">
	
	<table cellpadding='10' cellspacing='0' border='0' width='100%' align='center'>
	<tr>
	<td valign='top'>Life farming the fields here in the plains is hard and even dangerous, but sometimes I meet interesting people. I met one such recently.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
I was nearing my hut after another workday when I saw someone on the road up ahead. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
He had the look of another one of those adventurers who sometimes bring trouble so I was a bit apprehensive. He was very large, a barbarian from the frozen north a long way from home.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
He hailed me in a friendly manner and I relaxed a little. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
He offered to buy food and drink so I led him to my home. He tore into a stack of fresh fishwraps the wife had just made, with both hands stuffing his mouth as fast as he could. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
The wife grimaced at his lack of manners, but he had already paid me too much for the supplies so cleaning up a bit was no problem.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
He was, after all, a barbarian.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
As he ate I noticed a symbol he wore. Most people wear religious symbols but this one was unknown to me. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
As his eating slowed and he opened a mead (he had refused the offer of milk), I dared to ask him what it meant.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
"It is the symbol of the Blood Dancers, a guild of friends and travelers who think the same way I do," he replied.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
I produced a bottle of fish wine as he finished his drink and asked him to tell me more.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
"When I was just a kid, my grandfather told us about his days when he was young. Back then many of the animal races were much stronger than they are now. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
Some of the kobold and goblin clans and others would capture elves, humans, dwarves, and all the others, even some ogres and trolls, and enslaved them. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
One of their favorite cruel sports was making the slaves fight to the death in their arenas. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
The victors were then forced to dance for their masters in the blood-soaked earth of the arena floor. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
My grandfather was one of the slaves, he had helped to overthrow his evil masters one day when a raiding party attacked their stronghold."<br /><br />
<br /><br />
He held his medallion tightly as he stared at me. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
"What this means is freedom, at all costs. The old world, the old races, must fall. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
Kobolds,goblins, orcs, even the dragons and the gods shall pay for what has gone before. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
And the Blood Dancers will be there to make them pay!"<br /><br />
<br /><br />
He was silent a moment, then rose to go. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
He pressed a few more precious platinum in my hand as he instructed me to greet well any persons wearing the sign of the Blood Dancers.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
No matter their race or trade. I shall do  just that. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
For even a lowly tender of livestock such as myself is happy to know such brave and proud fighters as the <br /><br />
<br /><br />
Blood Dancers.</td>
